http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/%E2%80%98Target-set-for-welfare-depts.-will-be-achieved%E2%80%99/article14025959.ece

Adilabad Collector M. Jagan Mohan on Thursday assured Chief Secretary Rajiv Sharma that targets set under SC, BC and ST Welfare Departments would be achieved in time. He said bankers would be impressed upon to provide loans for governmental schemes in order to achieve the targets.At a video conference, the Collector said the target for the number of beneficiaries for the schemes under the Scheduled Caste Services Corporation was 3,117, but only 409 beneficiaries got financial assistance.Under the land purchase scheme of the 879 beneficiaries targeted during 2014-15 and 2015-16, only 314 could be provided 3 acre land each.The Project Officer of Integrated Tribal Development Agency, Utnoor, R.V. Karnan, said girls hostels will come up Adilabad, Utnoor, Boath, Khanapur and Luxettipet.The land for the purpose was currently being identified, he said.